==English==

===Etymology===
From Old French '''em''', ''in'', + '''brace?''', ''arm'', literally "in arms"; from Latin

===Verb===
'''embrace''', '''[[embraces]]''', '''[[embracing]]''', '''[[embraced]]'''

# [[hug]], put arms around
# ''(metaphorical)'' enfold, include

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[halata]] (1), [[syleillä]] (1)
*German: [[umarmen]] (1,2)

===Noun===
'''embrace''', '''[[embraces]]'''

# [[hug]] ''(noun)''; putting arms around someone
# ''(metaphorical)'' enfolding, including

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[syleily]] (1), [[halaus]] (1)
*French: [[embrasser]]

